{
  "abstract": "Xylella fastidiosa (Xf ) is a fastidious, xylem-inhabiting,\r\nGram-negative bacterium that causes serious plant\r\ndiseases in a wide range of plant species. The most serious\r\ndiseases are Pierce’s Disease (PD) of grape and Citrus\r\nVariegated Chlorosis (CVC). Functional genomic analyses\r\nof Xf have been severely limited by lack of a stable\r\nreplicative shuttle vector. Plamsid pUFR047, small,\r\nstable, wide host range, conjugative and repW shuttle\r\nvector have been successfully transferred into Xf strains\r\nby electroporation. The vector replicated in a stable\r\nmanner for over thirty generations of growth in the\r\nabsence of antibiotic selection in Xf strains.",
